SUMMARY:IU Global Learning Showcase
DESCRIPTION:May 1\, 2026\, 9:00 AM - 12:30 PMFerguson International Cente
 r\, 4th FloorPoster Set-up: 8:45ŌĆō9:20 AM  Light Breakfast: 9:00ŌĆō9:30 
 AM  Keynote Address: 9:30ŌĆō10:45 AM  Poster Session: 11:00 AM ŌĆō 12:30 
 PM  Join us for the IU Global Learning Showcase\, a celebration of studen
 t and faculty innovation in globally engaged education.  This year's keyn
 ote address\, "Reimagining Strategies Toward Sub-Saharan Africa: Opportun
 ities for U.S. Cities\, Communities\, and Universities\," will be deliver
 ed by Judd Devermont\, former National Security Council Senior Director f
 or African Affairs and National Intelligence Officer for Africa. He will 
 share lessons learned from drafting the Biden Administration's strategy t
 oward the region and discuss opportunities for Indiana's institutions\, l
 eaders\, and citizens to model a new\, more mutually advantageous partner
 ship.  After the keynote\, explore a poster sessionfeaturing presentation
 s from global client projects\, Collaborative Online International Learni
 ng (COIL)\, Diplomacy Lab\, and more. Topics span disciplines and highlig
 ht how IU students and faculty are turning learning into action on today'
 s most pressing global challenges.All are welcomeŌĆöcome be inspired and 
 join us in shaping a more connected world!Questions?&#160\; Email global@
 iu.edu (mailto:global@iu.edu) with "Global Learning Showcase" in the subj
 ect line.Supported by: IU Global\, the Center for the Study of Global Cha
 nge\, and the Hamilton Lugar School of Global and International Studies.
