 ic 250-foot long mural\, which originally wrapped around the entire exhib
 ition hall at the World's Fair\, depicts the social\, economic\, and cult
 ural history of Indiana from mound building to the 1930s. After several y
 ears of storage following the fair\, the panels were given to Indiana Uni
 versity in 1938\, where they were installed in three locations on the Blo
 omington campus.&#160\;</p><h4><strong>About Your Guide:</strong></h4><p>
